, and photos to explain topics under discussionCompanion files (with 100MB of videos, resources, recipes, fact sheets, and illustrations) are available for downloading by writing to the publisher at info@merclearning.com with proof of purchase. Selected FAQs Covered: Workings of the heart and the cardiovascular system; blood; coronary heart disease; risk factors; cholesterol (HDL and LDL); omega-3 fatty acids; exercises; fats; triglycerides; smoking; obesity and healthy diet; blood pressure and hypertension; diabetes; Body Mass Index; symptoms of a heart attack; arrhythmias; electrocardiograms; blood tests; post-traumatic stress disorder; emergency treatments; diagnoses; heart drug therapy and statins; stents; types of surgery (by-pass, angioplasty, etc.); pacemakers; risks of surgery; follow-up treatments; keys to healthy living; managing stress; glycemic index; carbohydrates, and more.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aHeartxDiseasesxPreventionvPopular works. 4aConsumer Health. 7aMEDICAL / Diseases.2bisacsh0 cEPUBz97819375859380 cprintz978193758590740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978193758592140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781937585921423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781937585921/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MDPM  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles